channel.title: About yourself
channel.description:
In all my time here I don't think iv ever seen a thread about peoples hobbies, ages, names and such. I would like to hear some about everyone. Ill start.
My names Jack, I am 16 years old and i live in Indiana. Some of my hobbies include motocross, wake boarding, barefoot skiing, and hunting/fishing. I have 2 older sisters both in college, and no you cant have there numbers. I plan on getting my pilots license soon. If theres anything else you want to know, just ask. Lets hear a bit about your selfs.

item.title: About yourself
item.dc:creator: @Thebeanie TheBeanie
item.description:
@Thebeanie wrote:

[quote=“Cowie`, post:46, topic:301858”][quote author=TheBeanie link=topic=398170.msg2956169#msg2956169 date=1252849205]
Im steve, 19, work at a social club for £7 an hour. I enjoy long distance riding and also riding through the pennines, im a night walker
[/quote]
Pennines you say. Where abouts do you go, through the radio signal station and down to the resevoirs?[/quote]

Well i go along the canal till i get to the junction for rippondon… i go up there its like 2 miles gradual up hill and then you get to Rippondon… Theres a big ass hill to climb thats steep for about 3/4 of a mile. then its flat where i stop off at a big Dam… Then i climb another big ass hill and then follow the moorland tracks off road along the hill range till i get to above where i live… then follow the track down.

And then theres just going on various tracks to lakes and stuff. Last week i rode to a lake which is about 15 mile from my house… Got there okay. got round the lake okay… then my back tire popped… One of the only times i didnt bring a puncture repair kit and a pump… had to get a local garage to pump it and ride like hell to the nearest train station about a mile away… waited 30 min for train got on it to find i didnt have enough for the ticket.
